derivation.yuyuan_name: early 16th cent. (as a noun in the sense 'wrinkle'): from Middle Dutch rompel

entry.tran: (因喜爱而)弄乱，抚弄(某人的头发)
entry.def: If you rumple someone's hair, you move your hand backwards and forwards through it as your way of showing affection to them.
